<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../922/23922.xml">
Princeton University</link></university>
 class of 1921, Cook was an engineer specializing in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../722/19722.xml">
metallurgy</link>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> He spent most of his working life at the American Brake Shoe Co. in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../989/124989.xml">
Mahwah, New Jersey</link></village>
, later consulting on the <work wordnetid="100575741" confidence="0.8">
